cctz
------------------------------------------
CCTZ contains two libraries that cooperate with <chrono> to give C++
programmers all the necessary tools for computing with dates, times, and time
zones in a simple and correct manner.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.3-1
  libcctz-devel-2.5-1bl1
  libcctz2-2.5-1bl1
  libgcc1-12.4.0-3
  libstdc++6-12.4.0-3
  pkg-config-2.4.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.44-1
  cmake-3.28.3-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  libbenchmark-devel-1.9.4-1bl1
  libgmock-devel-1.17.0-1bl1
  libgtest-devel-1.17.0-1bl1
  ninja-1.12.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/google/cctz

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/google/cctz/archive/refs/tags/v2.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cctz-2.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cctz-2.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cctz-2.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cctz-2.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcctz2-2.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcctz-devel-2.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(cctz)
  /usr/bin/time_tool.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/cctz.README
  /usr/share/doc/cctz/CONTRIBUTING.md
  /usr/share/doc/cctz/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/cctz/README.md

(libcctz2)
  /usr/bin/cygcctz-2.dll

(libcctz-devel)
  /usr/include/cctz/civil_time.h
  /usr/include/cctz/civil_time_detail.h
  /usr/include/cctz/time_zone.h
  /usr/include/cctz/zone_info_source.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/cctz/cctz-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/cctz/cctz-targets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/cctz/cctz-targets.cmake
  /usr/lib/libcctz.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/cctz.pc

